  "script": "A zoo lost a skunk? In Wisconsin, a skunk named Violet squeezed out of her enclosure — and now a whole city is on high alert. Officials are actually asking residents: if you see Violet, do not approach her, and whatever you do, do not make her feel cornered. Because the one animal you don't want trapped in your garage is the one that comes with a built-in chemical weapon. Keepers say she's tagged and probably tucked somewhere cool and dark, waiting out the daylight. No confirmed sightings yet. So a tiny striped fugitive is loose in the suburbs, fully armed, and the entire town is nervously sniffing the air. Would you really call the zoo if Violet turned up under your porch?",
